IFP President Emeritus and traditional Prime Minister of the AmaZulu, Prince Mangosuthu Buthelezi has been hospitalised. Prince Buthelezi’s family has confirmed that he has been admitted to undergo medical tests. Family spokesperson Dr Bhekuyise Ngqengelele Buthelezi says they have released a statement following media queries regarding his health. Prince Buthelezi has twice tested positive for COVID-19 but was reportedly asymptomatic. In a statement, the family says Buthelezi is undergoing medical tests after he experienced high blood pressure on Monday night. The statement says the doctors felt it’s wise for him to be admitted to hospital for all the necessary checks, as this would also allow him to get some much-needed rest.   